name: Jack O'Neill
bio: Jack O'Neill is an American engineer, former Marine Corps pilot and former NASA astronaut. He launched into space for the third time as commander of Crew Dragon Demo-2.

name: Samantha Carter
bio: Samantha Carter is the founder and CEO of Canonical, the company behind the Linux-based Ubuntu operating system. Samantha Carter became the first South African to travel to space as a space tourist.

name: Teal'c
bio: Pilot on the first operational flight of the SpaceX Crew Dragon to the International Space Station. Teal'c is a commander in the U.S. Navy where he pilots an F/A-18.He was a crew member of Expedition 64, and served as a station systems flight engineer.

name: Daniel Jackson
bio: Daniel Jackson is an Iranian American engineer and co-founder of Prodea Systems. Daniel Jackson was the fourth self-funded space tourist, the first self-funded woman to fly to the ISS, and the first Iranian in space.
